  "prompt": "What are some examples of player coming out of retirement after a long time?",
  "response": "There have been several notable instances of athletes coming out of retirement after a significant period of time. Here are some examples:\n\n### Football (Soccer)\n1. **Zinedine Zidane**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2006\n   - **Return Year**: Never officially returned to play, but came back to manage Real Madrid after retiring from playing.\n   \n2. **Paul Scholes**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2011\n   - **Return Year**: 2012 (returned to Manchester United after retiring for one season)\n\n### Basketball\n1. **Michael Jordan**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 1993 (first retirement)\n   - **Return Year**: 1995 (returned to the Chicago Bulls)\n   - **Second Retirement Year**: 1998\n   - **Second Return Year**: 2001 (returned to play for the Washington Wizards)\n\n2. **Allen Iverson**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2010\n   - **Return Year**: 2012 (returned to play in the Turkish Basketball League)\n\n### Baseball\n1. **Roger Clemens**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2003\n   - **Return Year**: 2004 (returned to play for the Houston Astros)\n\n2. **Brett Favre**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2008 (initial retirement)\n   - **Return Year**: 2008 (returned to the Green Bay Packers after initially announcing retirement)\n\n### Tennis\n1. **Kim Clijsters**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2007\n   - **Return Year**: 2009 (returned and won three more Grand Slam titles)\n\n2. **Bjorn Borg**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 1983\n   - **Return Year**: 1991 (returned to play on the ATP Tour but did not achieve his former success)\n\n### American Football\n1. **Deion Sanders**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2001\n   - **Return Year**: 2004 (returned to play for the Baltimore Ravens)\n\n2. **Brett Favre**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 2008 (initial retirement)\n   - **Return Year**: 2008 (returned to the Green Bay Packers after initially announcing retirement)\n\n### Golf\n1. **Tiger Woods**\n   - **Unofficial Retirement Period**: 2014-2017 (significant break from competitive golf due to injuries)\n   - **Return Year**: 2018 (returned and won the Tour Championship)\n\n2. **Greg Norman**\n   - **Retirement Year**: 1994 (partial retirement)\n   - **Return Year**: 2008 (returned to compete in the British Open)\n\nThese examples highlight the range of sports where athletes have returned to professional competition after a significant time away, often driven by personal motivation, changes in team dynamics, or shifts in their physical condition.",
